.TH CLUN 1 "0.2.1" "Clun 0.2.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clun \- JavaScript/TypeScript runtime and toolkit in pure Common Lisp
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clun
[\fIglobal-flags\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.br
.B clun
[\fIglobal-flags\fR] \fIfile\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Clun is a Bun-shaped JavaScript and TypeScript toolkit implemented entirely
in pure Common Lisp: runtime, package manager, test runner, bundler, HTTP
server, and related tooling. JavaScript is only what the user runs; Clun's
implementation is not Node, V8, libuv, Rust, Zig, or C.
.PP
This page is generated from the same command catalog as
.BR "clun --help"
and must stay synchronized with live CLI behavior.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B clun <file>
run a .js/.mjs/.cjs/.json/.ts file
.TP
.B clun run
run a file or package.json script
.TP
.B clun -e / -p
evaluate code (print awaited result)
.TP
.B clun exec
execute a Clun shell script
.TP
.B clun install
install deps, or add package(s) + install
.TP
.B clun add
add package(s) (-d dev, -E exact) + install
.TP
.B clun remove
remove a dependency + reinstall
.TP
.B clun publish
pack + publish to npm (NPM_TOKEN / .npmrc)
.TP
.B clun build
production bundle (Clun.build / Bun.build)
.TP
.B clun fmt / lint
format or lint JS/TS/JSON/YAML/CSS
.TP
.B clun compile
single-file executable
.TP
.B clun tsc
structural TypeScript typecheck
.TP
.B clun test
run the test runner
.TP
.B clun update
verify and activate latest Release bundle
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --cwd <dir>
